{A well-known position from the orthodox Queen's gambit declined. This
position, which has occured hundred of times in practise, provides an
excellent exmple of an active bishop. The problems facing both players are
clear-cut. White must play for a direct attack, to make the most from his
temporary advantage. Black still has to solve the problem of how to put his
Bishop to work.} 1... b5 {Black sets about it by force} 2. Bb3 2... b4 3. f6 {
