From the preceding examples we have seen that Black's chief trump card is his
action down the half-open c-file, with the eventual central advance ... Pd5,
also playing an important part  If, however, White succeeds in playing Pc4,
both these plans for Black are forestalled. He will not make much headway on
the c-file against White's bulward at c4, while the advance ... Pd5 will be,
to say the least, a difficult matter} 11. Bf4 Ne5 (11... Qb6+ 12. Kh1 d5 13.
