Qxg4 20. Qxb7 O-O 21. gxf6 $1) 20. Rxd5 Kd7 21. gxf6 Bxf6 22. g5 $1 22... Be7 (
22... Bg7 23. Rd3 23... -- 24. Rdh3 {winning the h-pawn
}) 23. Ke2 Raf8 24.
Be3 Rc8 25. b4 {Intending in due course to dissolve his doubled pawn by Pb5,
and saddle Black with a weak pawn on the Queenside  } 25... b5 {This should be
